{
  "stem": "322.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Mermelstein, since you can, you can prove to us that Jews were gassed in gas chambers at Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And if you did not, we will expose you to the mass media.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's the thing that didn't sit so well with me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So as a result of that, I looked for some lawyers to help me do something about that letter, because it was offensive and whatever else.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I couldn't get the proper help, but I finally did have one lawyer who, who said, look, we can do it, but you better prepare yourself for, for a sort of a, a, you know, a-- oh, I don't know, whatever.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They're going to have a panel and, and whatever.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in any case, that panel never came about.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They never even responded to our offer because this lawyer, Bill Cox, he, on my behalf, answered that letter and told them that they-- that we would do that, providing, you know, they will not renege their contract.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we got into a contract with them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They reneged the contract.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Took them to court.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the very first thing we won was a judicial notice from a judge in a court of law, in Superior Court, that indeed Jews were gassed in gas chambers in Auschwitz and that the Holocaust is not subject to dispute, and it is simply a fact.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And that rang a bell.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "That was, that was on October the 9th, 1991.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But of course, I didn't get the $50,000 then, because the judge did not want to get involved in anything other than just to take the judicial notice.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then, Mr.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Mermelstein, if you want to get your $50,000, you will have to litigate further.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Well, we did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We litigated until 1985, at which time we won.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
